{
  "_comment": "Composed HEAVY AIMLOps live-provision window — run in a DEDICATED window (crud_filter=gen-heavy-aimlops): provisions a REAL SKE cluster + nodepool AND then a REAL aimlops-platform release ON it, so it is the heaviest/most-billable chain in the suite (SKE create+release+teardown). Owner-approved cost + dedicated window. Adds a 4th concurrent VPC if mixed with the other heavy chains — keep it isolated.",
  "lifecycles": [
    {
      "id": "gen-heavy-aimlops",
      "service": "ai-ml/aimlops-platform",
      "enabled": true,
      "_note": "owner-approved live aimlops provision (2026-06-14): branch (1) adopt/create real SKE cluster then release aimlops on it. The SKE-create closure (keypair -> server-type/k8s-version/ske-image lookups -> security-group -> vpc -> subnet -> filestorage volume -> POST /v1/clusters -> POST /v1/nodepools) is copied FAITHFULLY from gen-heavy-ske-upgrade (same paths/bodies/captures/polling/expect_status/groups); the upgrade steps are intentionally omitted. After RUNNING, the 5 aimlops precondition GETs run against the REAL cluster_id (expect 200, tolerate 4xx), then GET images -> image_id, then POST /v1/aimlops-platform (UNPROVEN body — first live attempt) -> capture release_id -> poll ready -> PUT update -> DELETE. FULL teardown in reverse mirrors gen-heavy-ske so nothing leaks. || POST /v1/aimlops-platform body is UNPROVEN/first-live: NO data/api_bodies.json entry exists; field set (release_name/cluster_id/image_id/namespace/description + resource sizing) is best-effort from knowledge/formal/resources+services/ai-ml__aimlops-platform.yaml semantics. expect_status is broad so the first exploratory run RECORDS the real response without hard-failing.",
      "steps": [
        {
          "name": "create-keypair",
          "service": "virtualserver",
          "method": "POST",
          "path": "/v1/keypairs",
          "json": {
            "name": "regrkey{unique}",
            "tags": []
          },
          "expect_status": [
            200,
            201,
            202
          ],
          "capture": {
            "private_key": "$.private_key"
          },
          "cleanup": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "path": "/v1/keypairs/regrkey{unique}",
            "service": "virtualserver"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verify-keypair",
          "service": "virtualserver",
