          "path": "/v1/aimlops-platform/images",
          "expect_status": [
            200
          ],
          "capture": {
            "image_id": "$.images[0].id"
          },
          "_note": "image_id = $.images[0].id (same selector as the coverage lifecycle's list-images capture_soft). Required hard-capture: a release needs a real image_id."
        },
        {
          "name": "release-aimlops-platform",
          "method": "POST",
          "path": "/v1/aimlops-platform",
          "json": {
            "release_name": "regraimlops{ualpha}",
            "cluster_id": "{cluster_id}",
            "image_id": "{image_id}",
            "namespace": "regr-aimlops-{ualpha}",
            "description": "API regression suite — live provision",
            "cpu": "2",
            "memory": "4",
            "storage_class_name": "",
            "volume_size": "20"
          },
          "expect_status": [
            200,
            201,
            202,
            400,
            403,
            404,
            409,
            422
          ],
          "capture_soft": {
            "release_id": "$.id"
          },
          "_note": "UNPROVEN / FIRST-LIVE body. NO data/api_bodies.json entry exists for aimlops-platform. Field set is best-effort from knowledge/formal/resources/ai-ml__aimlops-platform.yaml (release_name/cluster_id/image_id/namespace/description proven-in-model) PLUS resource sizing (cpu/memory/storage_class_name/volume_size) inferred from the validate-resources precondition semantics — UNPROVEN guesses. expect_status is deliberately BROAD ([200,201,202,400,403,404,409,422]) so the first exploratory run RECORDS the real API response (incl. a 4xx that reveals the true required body) WITHOUT hard-failing the lifecycle and abandoning the live cluster. capture_soft (not hard capture) so a 4xx that yields no $.id leaves {release_id} literal -> the PUT/DELETE below 404 harmlessly and teardown still runs."
        },
        {
          "name": "wait-aimlops-release",
          "method": "GET",
          "path": "/v1/aimlops-platform/{release_id}",
          "expect_status": [
            200,
            400,
            403,
            404,
            409,
            422
          ],
          "optional": true,
          "group": "aimlops-release",
          "poll": {
            "field": "$.status",
            "until": [
              "READY",
              "Ready",
              "ready",
              "RUNNING",
              "Running",
              "ACTIVE",
              "Completed",
              "COMPLETED"
            ],
            "timeout": 1800,
            "interval": 30
          },
          "_note": "poll the release to a ready/running state. UNPROVEN poll: status field path ($.status) and ready enum are best-effort. optional+grouped+broad expect_status so a 404 (release never created on a 4xx POST) or an unexpected status field does not hard-fail before teardown."
        },
        {
          "name": "update-aimlops-platform",
          "method": "PUT",
          "path": "/v1/aimlops-platform/{release_id}",
          "json": {
            "description": "API regression suite — updated (live)"
          },
          "expect_status": [
            200,
            202,
            400,
            403,
            404,
            409,
            422
          ],
          "optional": true,
          "group": "aimlops-update",
          "_note": "in-place update (updateaimlopsplatformv1). UNPROVEN body (description-only guess). optional+broad: 404 if no real release_id was captured."
        },
        {
          "name": "delete-aimlops-platform",
          "method": "DELETE",
          "path": "/v1/aimlops-platform/{release_id}",
          "expect_status": [
            200,
            202,
            204,
            400,
            403,
            404,
            409,
            422
          ],
          "destructive": true,
          "retry_on_status": [
            409
          ],
          "retries": 40,
          "retry_interval": 30,
          "_note": "destructive teardown of the real release BEFORE the cluster is destroyed (a release on a deleted cluster would orphan). Targets the captured {release_id}; if none was captured (4xx POST) the literal placeholder 404s harmlessly. Broad expect_status + 409-retry so a still-provisioning release is reaped, not leaked."
        },
        {
          "name": "delete-ske-nodepool",
          "service": "ske",
          "method": "DELETE",
